\nassuming logical independence, we show that it is coherent to assess the\nprevisions of all the conjunctions by means of Minimum and Product t-norms. We\nverify by a counterexample that, when the previsions of conjunctions are\nassessed by the Lukasiewicz t-norm, coherence is not assured.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Oct 2020 15:44:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 10 Sep 2021 10:55:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-13"}
